  1. Latest News

  1. Exploratory work to begin on Vineyard and Church streets

    Exploratory work has begun by MIRA Image Construction LLC to confirm the location of existing underground utilities in Wailuku town as part of preparation work for infrastructure improvements. Read on...

  2. Mayor Victorino announces Public Works and Environmental Management director appointees

    Mayor Michael Victorino announced Monday afternoon that Rowena Dagdag-Andaya and Eric Nakagawa are his nominees as directors of the departments of Public Works and Environmental Management, respectively. Read on...

  3. Waiehu Municipal Golf Course Greens Renovation Phase II begins April 15

    The County of Maui Department of Parks and Recreation announced that the Waiehu Municipal Golf Course will begin renovating the front nine greens on April 15. Read on...

  4. Mayor Victorino proposes first budget for his administration

    Mayor Michael Victorino proposed his administration’s first budget to Maui County Council members on Monday afternoon, calling it a fiscally responsible and balanced spending program to invest in the future of Maui County. Read on...

  5. One-stop recruitment opportunity April 12 for lifeguard hopefuls

    Calling all lifeguard hopefuls: Maui County will hold a one-stop recruitment day April 12 for pool guard trainees. This could be a first step toward a career as a lifeguard. Read on...
